# Cloudflare Pages response headers.
#
# frame-ancestors lets ONLY the Medusa admin embed the storefront's /studio editor
# (the Shopify-style in-admin Theme Editor) and blocks all other framing (clickjacking).
# X-Frame-Options is intentionally omitted: it can't express a cross-origin allow-list,
# and SAMEORIGIN would break the admin iframe.
#
# PER-TENANT: replace https://medusa.edgepoint.work with the tenant's Medusa admin
# origin (e.g. https://eps-store-<tenant>.fly.dev) at onboard time.
#
# NOTE: this only takes effect when the storefront is served by Cloudflare Pages.
# On GitHub Pages custom headers are not supported; on the talos nginx container the
# equivalent is `add_header Content-Security-Policy "frame-ancestors 'self' https://medusa.edgepoint.work" always;`.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors 'self' https://medusa.edgepoint.work
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
